HEADWORD: Ironheads
<hw>I"ron*heads`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>A European composite herb (<spn>Centaurea nigra</spn>); -- so
called from the resemblance of its knobbed head to an iron ball fixed on
a long handle.</def> <rj><au>Dr. Prior.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Iron-hearted</ent>⟦br⟧
